https://miniwebtool.com/mac-address-generator/ ?

install Raspberry Pi full (with UI) on SD card

boot from SD card
 - > sudo apt update
 - > sudo apt upgrade
 - > sudo apt install gparted

add 'boot from SSD' feature - https://raspberrystreet.com/learn/how-to-boot-raspberrypi-from-usb-ssd

> sudo reboot

boot from SD card

install Raspberry Pi OS Lite on SSD drive: Lite version is a requirement to install 'Open Media Vault'
 - connet to Raspbery using VNC Client (or monitor)
 - open 'Accessories / Imager'
   - choose OS - "Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64-bit)" if your Raspbery is 8Gb, or "Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64-bit)" otherwise
   - choose storage (SSD drive)
   - (don't forget to enable SSH in settings)


reboot; boot from SSD (remove SD card)

connect to Raspberry using terminal on your machine and update it
 - > ssh pi@{ip}
 - > sudo apt update
 - > sudo apt upgrade
 - > sudo shutdown now

boot from SSD and recreate partitions
 - open 'System Tools / GParted'
 - select SSD drive
 - unmount 'rootfs' partion
 - resize 'rootfs' to 50Gb (51200 Mb) - OS File System
 - apply all operations
 - create new ext4 partition
 - format it (ext4)
 - apply all operations
 - label it 'data'
 - apply all operations
 - > sudo shutdown now

boot from SSD
 - > sudo fdisk -l 
 install 'Open Media Vault'
 - > wget -O - https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OpenMediaVault-Plugin-Developers/installScript/master/install | sudo bash
 - in case IP address has been changed, reconect 
 - > ssh pi@{new ip}
 - > sudo reboot

setup Open Media Vault (6th version)
 - open http://{ip}}/
   - username: admin
   - password: openmediavault
 - change default password
 - update OMV: System / Update Management / Updates / install updates

(almost operations in OMV should be applied and confirmed)

set Time Zone
 - System / Date & Time

disable root login
 - Services / SSH
   [ ] Permit root login

add groups / users
 - Users / Groups
        family
 - Users / Users

add File System 
 - Storage / File System / Mount /

add Shared Folders
 - Storage / Shared Folders / Create
   - homes    - Administrator: read/write, Users: read/write, Others: no access
   - docker   - Administrator: read/write, Users: read/write, Others: no access
   - torrent  - Administrator: read/write, Users: read/write, Others: no access
   - storage  - Administrator: read/write, Users: read/write, Others: no access
   - (copy absolute path for 'docker' shared folder)

enable home directries
 - Users / Settings / [x] Enable
 - (set location to 'homes' shared folder)

setup SAMBA
 - Services / SMB/CIFS / Settings
   [x] Enabled
 - Home directories
   [x] Enabled
   [ ] Browseable
   [x] Enable recycle bin; 


add SAMBA shares
 - Services / SMB/CIFS / Shares / create
   [x] Enabled
   set shared folder to 'storage'
   [x] Inherit ACLs
   [x] Inherit permissions
   [x] Enable recycle bin; 
       Retention time: 7

-- don not have access

install Docker
 - System / omv-extras / Docker
 - set Docker Storage to 'docker' shared folder 
 - save
 - install

install Portainer
 - System / omv-extras / Portainer
 - install


> sudo apt-get install mc

